This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

DomIQ Agentic PMS is a comprehensive property management CRM platform with AI-powered conversational capabilities. The system features sophisticated AI avatars, real-time lead engagement, analytics tracking, and embeddable widgets for external websites.

## Core Architecture

### 1. Dashboard CRM (`frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/`)
- Next.js 14 app with server components
- Supabase authentication with RBAC (super_admin, admin, agent roles)
- Real-time lead management and analytics
- Activity dashboard, contacts, call companion, settings pages

### 2. Database API (`backend/database-api/`)
- FastAPI backend managing PostgreSQL (Supabase hosted)
- **IMPORTANT**: Database is at api.domiq.ai, NOT localhost
- Handles authentication, profiles, call sessions, conversations, active calls
- RBAC middleware for all endpoints

### 3. Widget System
- Chat widget: `public/build/loader.js` - AI conversational interface
- Email widget: `public/build/email-loader.js` - Lead capture
- Vite-based bundling with CSS isolation (`domiq-` prefix)
- Session persistence across widget opens/closes

## Development Commands

### Dashboard Development
```bash
npm run dev                 # Start Next.js (port 4000)
npm run build              # Production build
npm run lint               # Run ESLint
npm run test:components    # Run Jest tests
```

### Database API
```bash
cd backend/database-api
source venv/bin/activate
python -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --reload --timeout-keep-alive 20
```
**Note**: Database is hosted at api.domiq.ai (starts with 3.1...), not localhost

